st century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Foliot was born about 1215, in Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Foliot, was 31 and his mother, Agnes of Thame, was 23. He married Agnes in 1245, in Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1268, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 54."},"et":{"Abt 1215–1268":"umbes 1215–1268","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1219–Female":"1219–Surnud","1247–1315":"1247–1315","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","1315":"1315","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1247":"1247","1268":"1268","1245":"1245","Abt 1215":"umbes 1215","1185":"1185","1194":"1194","17 January 1247":"17. jaanuar 1247","1219":"1219","Frisby, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England","Waterstoke Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1215–1268":"noin 1215–1268","1215–1268":"1215–1268","1219–Female":"1219–Kuollut","1247–1315":"1247–1315","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1247":"1247","1268":"1268","1245":"1245","Abt 1215":"noin 1215","1185":"1185","1194":"1194","17 January 1247":"17. tammikuuta 1247","1219":"1219","Frisby, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England":"Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England","Waterstoke Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"A